casebody.data:
James S. Virtue & Co., Limited, Respondent, v. Beacham, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

March 7, 1892.) Appeal from city court, general term.

Action by James S. Virtue & Co., Limited, against John Beacham. Argued before Daly, C. J., and Bischoff and Pryor, JJ.

P. Q. Eokerson, for appellant. P. Teoumseh Sherman, for respondent.

Ho opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs. See 17 H. Y. Supp. 450.
